The paper deals with the problem of inferring order from noisy information, which is a common problem in ranking applications. The paper presents polynomial time algorithms for solving the problem with high probability and shows that the maximum likelihood solution is close to the original permutation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
